{"label":"Create Playlist","list":[{"type":"passage","label":"Continents of the World","slug":"passage-template","editable":true,"data":{"title":"Continents of the World","text":"\nThe total land on the earth is formed of seven continents of various sizes. The seven continents of the world are:\n# 1. Asia\nAsia is the world's largest continent in size and population. The world's two most populous countries, China and India are in Asia.\n#India \nIndia is our country. India is known as the Land of unity in diversity as people from different religions, languages, cultures live united. India has 29 states and 7 union territories. New Delhi is the capital of India\n#2. Africa\nAfrica is the second largest continent of the seven continents of the world, The world's longest river the Nile and the world's largest desert the Sahara, both are home in Africa. \n# 3.North America\nNorth America is the third largest continent by area, following Asia and Africa. The largest fresh water lake, Lake Superior is located in this continent. The Mississippi - Missouri, is one of the longest river located in North America. \n# 4.South America\nThe world's largest river which is also the second longest is the Amazon river in South America. Brazil a country in South America is one of the largest coffee producer in the world. \n# 5.Antarctica\nAntarctica is the coldest continent on Earth. It is also called the White Continent or the Frozen Continent. Antarctica experiences half a year of sun light and half a year of complete darkness. Penguins are found in Antractica.\n# 6.Europe\nThe world's smallest country, the Vatican City, is in Europe. The Volga is one of the longest rivers in Europe. Finland, in Europe, is called the 'Land of Lakes' because melting ice sheets have created a lot of lakes here.\n#7. Australia\nAustralia is an Island continent covered with unique landscapes and natural wonders. The Great Barrier Reef, the pride and joy of Australia is made up of nearly 2,500 individual reefs and visible from space. Australia includes the islands of Tasmania and numerous small islands."},"id":"1597819263091"},{"label":"Choose the best answer - Continents of the World","type":"mcq","slug":"mcq","editable":true,"data":{"title":"Multiple Choice Questions","questions":[{"qText":"There are________ continents in the world.","options":"Seven,Five,Nine"},{"qText":"The largest continents is____________.","options":"Asia,Africa,North America"},{"qText":" ____________ is the longest river in the world","options":"Nile,Ganga,Kaveri"},{"qText":"Lake Superior is located in _________.","options":"North America,Australia,Europe"},{"qText":"Penguins are found in __________","options":"Antarctica,Asia,Africa"}]},"id":"1597819267441"},{"type":"match","label":"Match the Following - Continents of the World","slug":"match","editable":true,"data":{"title":"Match the words with same meaning.","text":"Asia,Biggest continent \nAfrica,Sahara desert \nEurope,Vatican city\nSouth America,Amazon forest\nAustralia,Kangaroo"},"id":"1597819272827"},{"label":"True or False - Continents of the World","type":"classifySentence","slug":"classify","editable":true,"data":{"title":"Classify the below sentences as Facts and Opinions","types":[{"name":"True","text":"India has one of the seven wonders of the world. \nBrazil is one of the largest coffee producer in the world.\nAntarctica has half year of light. "},{"name":"False","text":"Asia is the third largest continent. \nThe great barrier reef is in India."}]},"id":"1597819445020"}],"savePending":true,"id":"1597821414780","imported":true}